ZH: 我从山上滑下来时，坐在了一辆雪橇上。
EN: When I slid down the mountain, I was sitting on a sled.

ZH: 大家一起坐在雪橇上滑行，好玩极了！
EN: It's so much fun to ride together on a sled and slide down!

ZH: 这辆雪橇设计得非常结实，可以承受重压。
EN: This sled is designed very sturdy and can withstand heavy pressure.

ZH: 他们在雪地中竞赛，每人都有一辆雪橇。
EN: They are racing in the snow, each with their own sled.

ZH: 我们昨天去雪场滑雪，也体验了一下雪橇。
EN: We went skiing at the snow resort yesterday and also tried sledding.

ZH: 这个山坡太陡了，下坡时雪橇速度飞快。
EN: This hill is too steep, the sled goes down at a fast speed.

ZH: 小孩们在家附近的山坡上玩雪橇。
EN: The children are playing with sleds on the hill near their house.

ZH: 我给你买了一辆雪橇，希望你喜欢它。
EN: I bought you a sled, I hope you like it.

ZH: 这辆雪橇颜色非常鲜艳，很容易就能找到。
EN: This sled has a very bright color, it's easy to spot.

ZH: 那队选手利用雪橇比赛时，要保持平衡。
EN: When the athletes compete using sleds, they need to maintain balance.

ZH: 我们一起买了一辆大雪橇，可以一起滑行。
EN: We bought a large sled together, we can slide together.

ZH: 雪橇是一个很古老的冬季运动工具。
EN: A sled is a very old winter sports equipment.

ZH: 小狗跑到我的雪橇前面，拉着我走。
EN: The puppy ran to the front of my sled and pulled me along.

ZH: 他们从山顶放雪橇，一路滑到山脚下。
EN: They released the sled from the mountaintop, sliding all the way to the foot of the mountain.

ZH: 雪橇比滑雪板更容易控制，对初学者来说更方便。
EN: Sleds are easier to control than snowboards, making them more convenient for beginners.

ZH: 他们一边推着雪橇，一边欢声笑语地下山。
EN: They pushed the sled while laughing and cheering as they went down the mountain.

ZH: 雪橇比滑雪更适合小孩子，更加安全。
EN: Sledding is more suitable for children and is safer than skiing.

ZH: 在拐弯的时候，你需要用力转动雪橇来改变方向。
EN: When turning, you need to exert force to rotate the sled to change direction.

ZH: 滑雪场提供了租借雪橇的服务，你可以不用自己带。
EN: The ski resort provides rental sleds, so you don't have to bring your own.

ZH: 她骑着雪橇从顶端滑到了湖边的平地上。
EN: She rode the sled from the top and slid down to the flat ground near the lake.
